begin_memory_text: We talked about how she was learning fully online and how she attends a university in Michigan. She said it was difficult and I related to that how it is hard for kids with the COVID-19 pandemic. The sense of isolation is difficult.
middle_memory_text: We talked more about how she feels that work/life balance is hard to manage with working on the school newspaper, and I talked about how since people are home more due to COVID-19 some people expect you to be available at all times. That is difficult and makes it hard to manage work-life balance.
end_memory_text: We talked about how to find some positives in things and how COVID-19 will not last forever. We talked about how it might build resilience in people. We talked about how people might appreciate doing certain activities more once they are able to resume these activities.
rest_of_day_open: I think I will spend a lot of time at home. I will celebrate my son's birthday with the family. We plan to play games and get takeout from Longhorn. We will also have an Oreo cake. I hope he enjoys it! I will also walk along the canal with my kids, which will be a nice break.
critical_positive: I think we both had similar views on COVID. We both believed in the importance of wearing masks and socially distancing. I think we could relate to each other. We were both kind to each other. We did not interrupt one another. We did not have trouble coming up with topics.
critical_negative: Sometimes there were short awkward silences. We are at different life stages (I am much older than she is), so it was a little hard to relate to one another sometimes. I wasn't sure how interested she was when I talked about my kids, and we did not talk about much other than COVID-19.

begin_memory_text: We talked about how we were doing today and about what we would do on the weekend.
middle_memory_text: We talked about what college classes were like for students right now with things being remote and what that was like, also about how that was affecting people's moods in our areas.
end_memory_text: We talked about how things were like before COVID-19 for families (how some things were taken for granted) and about our hopes that things would get better and we would be able to do the things we used to, such as have classes in-person, and physical things at entertainment events like bowling alleys.
rest_of_day_open: I think it's going to be a good week, I have things I need to get done and will be busy but I feel prepared to take it all on. I foresee myself having time to relax and being able to be productive. I am anticipating good things and not expecting anything negative to happen.
critical_positive: I think what worked was we were both willing to talk about ourselves (to an extent). I am normally reserved but I thought it would be good to talk a bit more about where I was and myself as a student to get my conversation partner to feel more comfortable talking with me. She was easy to talk to and willing to express herself too, which was nice to hear.
critical_negative: I wanted to talk about topics that were a bit less neutral politically but didn't want to bring it up because I thought that might not be a pleasant conversational topic. Also I avoided talking about things that might be perceived as negative or not politically neutral, which I didn't mind, but I would have been interested in finding out her opinion on them if we had time.
